	<item>
		<title>Comment on The History of Reading by jbryan</title>
		<link>http://lifeandmusic.loricarson.com/?p=134#comment-468</link>
		<dc:creator>jbryan</dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 02 Nov 2010 00:52:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://lifeandmusic.loricarson.com/?p=134#comment-468</guid>
		<description>Two of the greatest gifts of being alive are reading and music....music and reading. If I had to pick one over the other it would be like choosing between two children but ultimately it would be music for me, hands down. But reading is music&#039;s siamese twin for what it does to the mind and soul. Reading offers symmetry to the chaos of real life.

That said I have missed your reading recommendations. I always hoped you wouls start a reading blog one day. I loved the reference to your reading in your journal of old. You turned me on to some great novels......and Alice Munro! Thank you for her!

I just so happen to be reading Great House.  Stunning.</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Two of the greatest gifts of being alive are reading and music&#8230;.music and reading. If I had to pick one over the other it would be like choosing between two children but ultimately it would be music for me, hands down. But reading is music&#8217;s siamese twin for what it does to the mind and soul. Reading offers symmetry to the chaos of real life.</p>
<p>That said I have missed your reading recommendations. I always hoped you wouls start a reading blog one day. I loved the reference to your reading in your journal of old. You turned me on to some great novels&#8230;&#8230;and Alice Munro! Thank you for her!</p>
<p>I just so happen to be reading Great House.  Stunning.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
