		<description>I remember reading a journal of a 19th century novelist.  The name escapes me now, but it doesn&#039;t matter.  Anyway, his daily entries were full of the details of his day with little discussion of his work except to say &quot;wrote four pages.&quot;  And that&#039;s each daily entries ended.  4 pages, 3 pages, 5 pages.  Good writing is a journey that can&#039;t be rushed, it can only be paced.</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I remember reading a journal of a 19th century novelist.  The name escapes me now, but it doesn&#8217;t matter.  Anyway, his daily entries were full of the details of his day with little discussion of his work except to say &#8220;wrote four pages.&#8221;  And that&#8217;s each daily entries ended.  4 pages, 3 pages, 5 pages.  Good writing is a journey that can&#8217;t be rushed, it can only be paced.</p>
